"title": "5740: virgin",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5740: virgin",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Generally a young person, especially a female, who has not had sexual intercourse. Virginity is an important quality in a bride, and its surrender or violation prior to marriage is sternly condemned. In the miracle of the incarnation, Mary was still a virgin when Jesus Christ was conceived. Virginity is also used metaphorically to denote purity and innocence.</p>\n<h2>Virginity is important in a bride</h2>\n<h3>Virgins were sought as brides</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:14-Gen24:16\">GEN 24:14–24:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:12\">SNG 4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:42-Gen24:45\">GEN 24:42–24:45</a> <em>The word translated “maiden” might also refer to a virgin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:13-Lev21:14\">LEV 21:13–21:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:19\">DEU 22:13–22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:2\">EST 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:17\">EST 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:5\">ISA 62:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:22\">EZK 44:22</a></p>\n<h3>The church presented as a virgin bride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:2\">2CO 11:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7-Rev19:8\">REV 19:7–19:8</a></p>\n<h2>The loss of virginity before marriage</h2>\n<h3>Of a virgin not pledged in marriage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:16-Exod22:17\">EXO 22:16–22:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:28-Deut22:29\">DEU 22:28–22:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:12-2Sam13:16\">2SA 13:12–13:16</a></p>\n<h3>Of a virgin pledged in marriage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:20-Deut22:21\">DEU 22:20–22:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:23-Deut22:24\">DEU 22:23–22:24</a> <em>Betrothal was as serious a commitment as marriage itself; consorting with another person during this period was tantamount to adultery</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:25-Deut22:27\">DEU 22:25–22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18-Matt1:19\">MAT 1:18–1:19</a></p>\n<h3>Some fathers surrendered their daughters' virginity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:8\">GEN 19:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:24\">JDG 19:24</a></p>\n<h2>Particular roles involving virgins</h2>\n<h3>Maidens in victory processions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:25\">PSA 68:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:4\">JER 31:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:20-Exod15:21\">EXO 15:20–15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:34\">JDG 11:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6\">1SA 18:6</a></p>\n<h3>Virgins as bridesmaids</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:14\">PSA 45:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1\">MAT 25:1</a></p>\n<h3>A virgin looked after King David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:1-1Kgs1:4\">1KI 1:1–1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Virginity as a sign of purity and innocence</h2>\n<h3>Virgins were spared after military victories</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:17-Num31:18\">NUM 31:17–31:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:11-Judg21:12\">JDG 21:11–21:12</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's virgin purity lost</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:13\">JER 18:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:21-Jer31:23\">JER 31:21–31:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:3-Ezek23:8\">EZK 23:3–23:8</a></p>\n<h2>Virginity as a metaphor for (apparent) inviolability</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:21\">2KI 19:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:22\">ISA 37:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:1\">ISA 47:1</a></p>\n<h2>Lost opportunities of virgin youthfulness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:2\">AMO 5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:36-Judg11:40\">JDG 11:36–11:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:12\">ISA 23:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:11\">JER 46:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:15-Lam1:16\">LAM 1:15–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:13\">LAM 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:8\">JOL 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Paul's advice about virgins</h2>\n<h3>A virgin is freer to serve God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:32-1Cor7:35\">1CO 7:32–7:35</a></strong> <em>The unmarried have fewer responsibilities and worldly cares and so may offer undivided devotion to God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:25-1Cor7:28\">1CO 7:25–7:28</a></p>\n<h3>Remaining unmarried is a preferred option</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:8\">1CO 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:37-1Cor7:38\">1CO 7:37–7:38</a></p>\n<h3>Marriage is the proper outlet for sexual passion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:9\">1CO 7:9</a> <em>Though Paul urges abstinence, sexual passion is not wrong; however, sexual relationships must be confined to marriage</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:36\">1CO 7:36</a></p>\n<h2>Mary's virginity at Jesus Christ's conception</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:20-Matt1:25\">MAT 1:20–1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:27\">LUK 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:34-Luke1:35\">LUK 1:34–1:35</a></p>\n<h2>Parable of the ten virgins</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1-Matt25:13\">MAT 25:1–25:13</a></p>",
